key_points: Claims that U.S. Navy SEALs rescued over a thousand trafficked children from the Ever Given ship in the Suez Canal are false.
The story originated from Before It's News, a website known for publishing false and misleading content.
No credible news publisher or government entity confirmed the story of the rescue operation.
The Ever Given cargo ship became stuck in the Suez Canal in March 2021, causing a significant maritime traffic jam.
The false story also claimed that Weapons of Mass Destruction were found on the ship.
It was also falsely stated that the ship was co-owned by Walmart and the Clinton Foundation, implicating them in an international child trafficking ring.
The story suggested that trafficked children were ordered through catalogs like Wayfair by pedophiles.
There was a mention of a non-existent 'telegram' claiming the U.S. Navy SEALs had found live and dead children in cargo containers.
Similar baseless trafficking claims were made about the Wayfair online shopping website in July 2020.
The article aims to debunk the false narrative by providing facts and pointing out the lack of credible reporting on the matter.
